description: In this project, the problem is to employ machine learning strategies, especially clustering, to group cricket players into distinct performance-based categories. The intent is to transcend the usual statistics and reveal the concealed performance frameworks that the selectors, coaches, and analysts can use to make their decisions more effectively.

An image analysis framework, Fibril Analysis for Cellulose Technology (FACT), which utilizes machine learning (ML) segmentation and morphological thinning, to measure the fibril width distribution of cellulose nanofibers (CNFs) from negative contrast scanning electron microscopy (NegC-SEM) images. This application was developed in Mathematica V13.
An AI based Smart Waste Classification System built on top of Python's Web Framework Django with several Web Technologies  with additional techs of Machine Learning models
In this repository different AI/ML algorithms are implemented by using PyTorch framework for learning purpose.

An advanced machine learning framework using XGBoost to predict corporate default risk. Features a Streamlit dashboard for real-time risk assessment, detailed financial visualizations, and an automated benchmark of 13 ML algorithms. Replaces subjective judgment with data-driven probability.
MLOps-Driven Machine Learning Framework for Predicting Ocean Oxygen Saturation Using Underwater Wireless Sensor Networks

BiggerFish is a research framework for machine learning-based side-channel attacks. It demonstrates how CPU performance patterns can be used to identify websites with up to 87.3% accuracy, bypassing VPNs and private browsing.

VeriCredit is an enterprise-grade AI governance framework designed to evaluate, validate, and audit AI-generated credit decision explanations produced by Large Language Models (LLMs). The system ensures that credit explanations are faithful to underlying machine learning models, free from bias, legally compliant, and stable across prompts.

This repository contains a collection of Python programs and Jupyter notebooks focusing on Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) algorithms. It covers implementations, experiments, and hands-on code examples using popular libraries and frameworks in Python.

Unsupervised machine learning and geospatial analytics framework for clustering global cities based on sustainability, ESG, infrastructure, and climate-resilience indicators to support smart-city planning and public-policy decision modeling.
An open-source framework for machine learning and other computations on decentralized data.
Discover key research papers on Quantum Machine Learning (QML) and explore transfer learning frameworks, applications, and optimization strategies.
This project develops a predictive framework for credit risk under IFRS 9 standards. It leverages a dataset of over 32,500 entries to predict the Probability of Default (PD).
A machine learning framework using active learning strategies to accelerate the design of BCC solid solution high-entropy alloys
A machine learning framework in Zig.
Machine Learning Framework for the Rapid Detection of Dengue Fever via CBC Parameters.

PredictThenOptimize framework for nurse staffing under demand uncertainty, combining machine learning demand forecasting with mixed-integer optimization to analyze how forecast errors, noise, and demand drift impact staffing decisions and operational cost.
Distributed service framework using asynchronous messages supporting IoT, Machine Learning and Video
A Machine Learning framework to predict nuclear stability using XGBoost and the NUBASE2020 dataset, featuring SMOTE for class balancing and physics-informed feature analysis.
Autoware-ML is a machine learning framework for multiple tasks, supporting the full lifecycle - training, evaluation, optimization, and deployment of models with native runtime support in Autoware.
Interactive assessment framework for scoping AI, machine learning and data science projects for social good organizations.
ML.NET is an open source and cross-platform machine learning framework for .NET.
End to End Machine learning projects of Finance analytics in CRISP DM Framework
This is the official repository for CardioLab. A machine and deep learning framework for the estimation and monitoring of laboratory abnormalities throught ECG data.
Tech Soft 3D tutorials of python CAD framework for machine learning development. Requires HOOPS AI
TAK-ML - A machine learning framework for use with the TAK ecosystem (specifically ATAK and TAK Server at the moment)

Temporal machine learning framework for early sepsis risk prediction based on multivariate ICU time-series data, leveraging a stacked (LSTM) architecture. Beyond retrospective evaluation, the model was deployed within a lightweight mobile application, enabling real-time inference, and visualization of short-term risk trajectories.

A physics-informed, data-driven framework integrating Silvaco ATLAS TCAD simulations with advanced machine learning models for fast and accurate prediction of Double-Gate Tunnel FET (DG-TFET) electrical characteristics.

This project presents a hybrid AIOps framework that enhances the reliability of cloud-native systems by integrating Kubernetes autoscaling with machine learning-based anomaly detection and remediation. The framework enables autonomous system management, reducing downtime and improving performance through proactive and intelligent operations.

MPMR-IMCP is a two-stage AI framework. It first uses a Vision Transformer to identify mucin expression from H&E whole slide images, then applies machine learning to integrate image features and clinical data for predicting intestinal metaplasia cancer risk.

FairML is a toolkit for auditing and visualizing fairness in machine learning models. It provides bias detection, synthetic bias injection, standard fairness metrics, a modular testing framework, and an interactive Streamlit dashboard for exploring model behavior.

A neural network that analyzes a toy data set of heights and weights, mapping them to genders. This was done without the help of machine learning frameworks to deeply understand how a neural network learns.
Foam-Agent: An end-to-end, composable multi-agent framework for automating CFD simulations in OpenFOAM. NeurIPS 2025 Machine Learning and the Physical Sciences Workshop.
PArallel Distributed Deep LEarning: Machine Learning Framework from Industrial Practice &
Hybrid Vision Transformer and Machine Learning framework for automated road damage detection

A research-focused multimodal machine learning framework for clinical outcome prediction, integrating medical imaging and tabular clinical features with reproducible training and explainable AI components.

Machine learning project for automated detection and classification of cardiac arrhythmias from ECG data. Implements preprocessing, feature extraction, and ML models to identify abnormal heart rhythms including atrial fibrillation, tachycardia, and other patterns. Built with Python, scikit-learn, and deep learning frameworks.

I'm a Results-driven Software Engineer with expertise in computer vision and machine learning applications. My journey in tech has been fueled by a passion for creating intelligent systems that solve real-world problems.  With a strong background in Python programming, deep learning frameworks, and image processing technologies.

A machine learning pipeline for early lung cancer risk assessment using patient clinical and lifestyle data. This project implements a classification framework to predict cancer presence based on features like smoking history, age, respiratory symptoms, and demographic factors
A pipeline framework for developing video and image processing application. Supports multiple GPUs and Machine Learning tooklits
Basic Python Code, Machine Learning, Searching Algorithms, DI, Library, Framework

A machine learningbased malware detection framework was developed to classify benign and malicious executables. Selected discriminative features were used to train multiple classifiers. Evaluation using accuracy and ROCAUC shows that ensemble models achieve superior detection performance.

AI-based real-time insider threat detection system that analyzes network traffic and user behavior using machine learning models. The framework integrates multiple data sources, generates severity scores, and triggers automated email alerts for proactive cybersecurity response.
Automated modeling and machine learning framework FEDOT

Space Labs AI presents: A radiation-tolerant machine learning framework enabling neural networks to operate reliably in space environments. Features adaptive protection, Reed-Solomon error correction, and breakthrough architecture optimizations that improve performance under radiation.
Behavioral Vulnerability Assessment Framework for IoT-Based Satellite Systems Using Machine Learning
Distributed tensors and Machine Learning framework with GPU and MPI acceleration in Python

Quantrisk-ML is a Python-based framework combining machine learning (LSTM, Random Forest) with quantitative finance to analyze portfolio risk, forecast returns, compute VaR, run Monte Carlo simulations, and stress-test scenarios for data-driven financial insights.

Python-based multi-stage framework for daily rainfall time-series reconstruction in seasonal tropical forest ecosystems using unsupervised anomaly detection, bias-corrected reanalysis and satellite data, and multi-objective machine learning selection.

This project is a Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) and Machine Learning Tool for Predicting CO Equivalent Emissions in the Textile Industry. It provides a data-driven framework to analyze and forecast the environmental impact of various textile materials and processes.
A comprehensive portfolio optimization framework implementing multiple optimization techniques including genetic algorithms, mean-variance optimization, risk parity, and machine learning approaches.
Open-source framework for monitoring woody plant encroachment using Sentinel-2, spectral indices, and machine learning (RF & XGBoost)
Exploratory computational framework for protein sequence modeling and folding analysis using machine learning and simulations.

A Python-based framework for detecting anomalies in textual data using NLP, machine learning, and deep learning. Implements unsupervised and supervised models, transformer-based embeddings (BERT, RoBERTa), and geospatial analysis to enable automated content verification, trend monitoring, and location-based anomaly detection.

This repo features the code, input and output files for my undergraduate thesis titled "Design and optimization of an integrated computational and machine learning framework to detect functional variants and elucidate their contributions to biological pathways".
Machine learning framework for real-time cancer risk prediction with adaptive self-training feedback.

Application Deployment and Description  To deploy the application, I used Streamlit, a Python-based framework designed for rapid development of interactive data science and machine learning applications. Streamlit allows users to input data through a web interface and obtain real-time predictions along with explanations.

Petastorm library enables single machine or distributed training and evaluation of deep learning models from datasets in Apache Parquet format. It supports ML frameworks such as Tensorflow, Pytorch, and PySpark and can be used from pure Python code.

This repository contains educational materials and code examples for learning TensorFlow, a popular open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides hands-on examples covering fundamental machine learning concepts, TensorFlow basics, and core learning algorithms.
This repo contain the jupyter scripts for Perceptron leaning algo and Adaline Algorithm using both scikit learn library and writting functions and also files of scikitlearn, tensorflow and keras
The PennyLane-Qrack plugin integrates the Qrack quantum computing framework with PennyLane's quantum machine learning capabilities.

Machine learning framework for inflammation severity assessment using histopathology features, implementing GroupKFold cross-validation, Pipeline structure, feature selection, ensemble models, hyperparameter tuning, and SHAP-based interpretability for multi-class and binary classification tasks.

This project builds a complete data pipeline using NumPy only  no Pandas, no sklearn, no ML frameworks. It simulates a real Machine Learning preprocessing workflow entirely from scratch to develop deep intuition before training actual models.

A comprehensive, production-ready framework for time series forecasting in financial markets. This project demonstrates modern machine learning techniques for predicting stock prices and evaluating trading strategies with realistic backtesting.

NRLMF-DTI-MurrayaBAT is a drugtarget interaction framework that applies NRLMF-based negative inference to address data imbalance and employs supervised machine learning to predict interactions between Murraya paniculata bioactive compounds and brown adipose tissueassociated proteins in obesity-related conditions.

MetaMorph is an open-source framework that leverages the power of Large Language Models (LLMs) to process, extract, and transform messy, unstructured, or heterogeneous columns of metadata into structured, machine-readable formats to enhance machine learning pipelines and predictive models across any domain.
A network automation framework for Cisco iOS device splitting and monitoring with an integrated machine learning algorithm

his repository contains a research project focused on forecasting Bitcoin (BTCUSD) prices using the ARIMA (AutoRegressive Integrated Moving Average) model within a machine learning framework. The project explores the challenges of cryptocurrency volatility and demonstrates how ARIMA can be applied to timeseries data for financial forecasting.
Machine learning framework for building specialist models.

An AI-driven adaptive honeypot framework that dynamically deceives attackers, analyzes behavior using machine learning and reinforcement learning, and generates actionable threat intelligence mapped to the MITRE ATT&CK framework.
This repository seeks to leverage machine learning frameworks to tackle Valley Fever disease. Goal is to identify compounds that inhibit the disease.

Machine learning framework for predicting N-glycosylation sites in therapeutic antibodies and lectin-glycan interactions, enabling automated design of antibody effector functions and immune cell trafficking.
From-scratch implementations of core concepts in machine learning, math, and programming. No frameworks unless necessary  just fundamentals, step by step.
Atlantic: Automated Data Preprocessing Framework for Machine Learning
Predict football match outcomes using the W-5 Multi-Agent AI Consensus Framework, achieving high accuracy with a blend of AI and machine learning techniques.
this model predicts the bandgap using machine learning framework , and is developed by KNN algorithm.

Developed a Fake Currency Detection System utilizing continual learning and incremental training techniques within deep learning frameworks. Demonstrated proficiency in deploying adaptable machine learning models for real-time currency verification.
This Repository you can see the document and data used in this research "Data-driven machine-learning framework for faade-level visual comfort mapping at the urban-block scale"
Basic on-chip machine learning framework for System-on-Chip (SoC) FPGAs using Direct Memory Access.

An acausal modeling framework for automatically parallelized scientific machine learning (SciML) in Julia. A computer algebra system for integrated symbolics for physics-informed machine learning and automated transformations of differential equations

End-to-end machine learning pipeline with automated data preprocessing, model training, hyperparameter tuning, deployment, and monitoring. Supports multiple ML frameworks including TensorFlow, PyTorch, and scikit-learn.
A comprehensive machine learning framework for cryptocurrency price prediction using advanced time series models and financial metrics evaluation.

A fast, distributed, high performance gradient boosting (GBT, GBDT, GBRT, GBM or MART) framework based on decision tree algorithms, used for ranking, classification and many other machine learning tasks.

The Multi-Agent RLRM (Reinforcement Learning with Reward Machines) Framework is a library designed to facilitate the formulation of multi-agent problems and solve them through reinforcement learning. The framework supports the integration of Reward Machines (RMs), providing a modular and flexible structure for defining complex tasks.

This project is a Smart Home Energy Saving application designed to optimize energy consumption in smart homes. It is built using a combination of machine learning models and generative AI, leveraging a multi-agent framework (Microsoft Agent Framework).

BrainwaveAI is an artificial intelligence project focused on building intelligent systems that learn from data and adapt over time. It provides a clean, modular framework for experimenting with machine learning and deep learning models, making it suitable for learning, research, and real-world AI applications.
An intelligent data collection and preprocessing framework for predicting house prices using machine learning techniques.
Realistic early elephant flow detection using a two-stage incremental machine learning framework with strict data-leakage prevention and deployment-ready ONNX models.
A differentiable ray tracer using the PyTorch machine-learning framework in Python.

This is the first release of the Variational Spectral Learning code (reference implementation) used to generate the figures/analyses in the manuscript titled "Variational (Energy-Based) Spectral Learning: A Machine Learning Framework for Solving Partial Differential Equations".

An advanced cryptocurrency trading bot and predictive analysis framework exploring the potential of automated "passive income" through machine learning. Features implementation of XGBoost, Random Forest, Transformer, and Reinforcement Learning for signal generation
A Machine Learning-powered cybersecurity framework designed to safeguard sensitive healthcare data by predicting threats and detecting network anomalies in real-time.

A privacy-preserving machine learning framework for detecting malicious network flows from encrypted traffic metadata. Includes Random Forest, SGD, and XGBoost models, cross-dataset evaluation, live inference simulation, and SIEM-compatible alert export.

A Java-based Object-Oriented Programming project that implements the Naive Bayes classifier from scratch to detect phishing emails. The project emphasizes clean class design, encapsulation, modularity, and algorithmic clarity while avoiding third-party machine learning frameworks.
[Research Article] Machine learning-based prediction and optimisation framework for as-extruded cell viability in extrusion-based 3D bioprinting
Machine-learning framework for predicting phenotypic traits in Metschnikowia pulcherrima
